@startuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

participant "Host Origen\n(192.168.1.5)" as A
participant "Switch / Red" as S
participant "Host Destino\n(192.168.1.10)" as B
participant "Otros Hosts" as C

Note over A: Consulta caché ARP:\nMAC desconocida para .10

== Proceso ARP Request ==

A -> S: ARP Request (Broadcast)
Note right of A: Frame Eth: Dest=FF:FF:FF:FF:FF:FF\n"¿Quién es 192.168.1.10? Avisar a .5"

S -> B: Reenvío Broadcast
S -> C: Reenvío Broadcast

Note over C: IP no coincide.\nDescartar paquete.

== Proceso ARP Reply ==

Note over B: IP coincide.\nActualiza tabla ARP con MAC de A.

B -> S: ARP Reply (Unicast)
Note left of B: Frame Eth: Dest=MAC_A\n"Soy 192.168.1.10, mi MAC es BB:BB..."

S -> A: Reenvío Unicast

Note over A: Recibe respuesta.\nGuarda MAC de B en caché.

== Envío de Datos ==

A -> B: Paquete IP (Encapsulado en Ethernet con MAC_B)
@enduml
